STAY HERE.

241
00:10:10,068 --> 00:10:12,696
DO THIS INTERNSHIP
AT MY DAD'S FIRM.

242
00:10:12,779 --> 00:10:14,781
I THINK THIS IS
WHAT'S BEST RIGHT NOW.

243
00:10:14,865 --> 00:10:18,452
OH, TOTALLY.
WAY BETTER THAN WALKING.

244
00:10:18,535 --> 00:10:20,495
LOOK, IT'S NOT ABOUT
THE SHORT TERM, OKAY?

245
00:10:20,579 --> 00:10:21,872
IT'S ABOUT THE LONG TERM.

246
00:10:21,955 --> 00:10:24,291
ME AND MY FAMILY,
WE'VE HAD THIS HUDSON PLAN.

247
00:10:24,374 --> 00:10:26,210
THIS INTERNSHIP JUST
GIVES ME A LEG UP.

248
00:10:26,293 --> 00:10:28,462
PUN INTENDED OR...?

249
00:10:30,672 --> 00:10:34,843
LOOK, I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU HAVE TO CHOOSE?

250
00:10:34,927 --> 00:10:38,013
SEEMS LIKE YOU CAN
AFFORD BOTH.

251
00:10:38,972 --> 00:10:40,265
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

252
00:10:40,349 --> 00:10:41,266
COME ON.

253
00:10:41,350 --> 00:10:42,893
GOING TO LIVE
IN NEW YORK?

254
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:44,811
THAT CAN'T BE
THAT CHEAP.

255
00:10:44,895 --> 00:10:46,313
WELL, WE CAN SPLIT
THE RENT?

256
00:10:46,396 --> 00:10:47,814
OH... SURE.

257
00:10:49,483 --> 00:10:51,318
BUT WALKING THROUGH
CENTRAL PARK

258
00:10:51,401 --> 00:10:52,319
WON'T BE AS MUCH FUN

259
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:54,988
IF I HAVE TO PUSH YOU
IN YOUR WHEELCHAIR.

260
00:10:56,448 --> 00:10:59,368
I THINK THAT'S CALLED
"CONDITIONAL LOVE".

261
00:10:59,451 --> 00:11:00,410
WHAT?

262
00:11:00,494 --> 00:11:02,538
I HAVE AN APPLICATION
TO HAND IN.

263
00:11:02,621 --> 00:11:04,706
TRINA:
JIMMY, WAIT.

264
00:11:05,832 --> 00:11:08,001
THAT CAME OUT WRONG.

265
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:18,178
(PASS CARD BEEPS)

266
00:11:28,981 --> 00:11:31,275
(COMPUTER KEYS CLACK)

267
00:11:38,657 --> 00:11:40,617
(UNINTELLIGIBLE MUMBLE)

268
00:11:48,709 --> 00:11:50,127
(GRUNT OF EFFORT)

269
00:11:52,671 --> 00:11:53,922
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

270
00:11:54,006 --> 00:11:55,841
JIMMY:
YEAH, EVERYTHING'S FINE.

271
00:11:55,924 --> 00:11:58,719
YOUR DAD TOLD ME
WHAT HAPPENED.

272
00:11:58,802 --> 00:11:59,887
HE DID?

273
00:12:03,932 --> 00:12:06,310
SWEETIE, I KNOW IT'S NOT
THE ANSWER YOU WANTED,

274
00:12:06,393 --> 00:12:07,978
BUT STEM CELL SURGERY?

275
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:10,147
COME ON, THAT'S NOT SOMETHING
YOU JUST RUSH INTO.

276
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:11,398
NOT NOW.

277
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:14,484
THAT. YEAH,

278
00:12:14,568 --> 00:12:16,361
YOU'RE RIGHT.

279
00:12:16,445 --> 00:12:17,362
OKAY?

280
00:12:17,446 --> 00:12:19,489
OKAY.

281
00:12:19,573 --> 00:12:21,825
(BELL RINGS)

282
00:12:21,909 --> 00:12:22,534
MRS. BROOKS:
BYE, SWEETIE.

283
00:12:22,618 --> 00:12:23,285
BYE, MOM.

284
00:12:24,119 --> 00:12:26,288
(PLAYING '50S-STYLE BALLAD)

285
00:12:32,085 --> 00:12:34,004
♪ NO ONE CAN STOP ♪

286
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:36,381
♪ OUR INTER-LOCKER LOVE ♪

287
00:12:38,884 --> 00:12:41,220
♪ NO ONE CAN STOP
OUR... ♪

288
00:12:43,472 --> 00:12:44,640
WHAT'S WRONG?
WE HAD IT.

289
00:12:44,723 --> 00:12:48,560
SORRY. DO WE GO FROM THE "A"
TO THE "F" OR...?

290
00:12:49,228 --> 00:12:50,437
I DON'T KNOW CHORDS,
DUDE.

291
00:12:50,521 --> 00:12:51,688
SPINNER'S RIGHT,
WE'RE LAME.

292
00:12:51,772 --> 00:12:55,484
NO, WE'RE NOT LAME.
WE CAN'T BE LAME.

293
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:56,610
SAV, PLAY A CHORD.

294
00:12:56,693 --> 00:12:57,903
ANY CHORD.

295
00:12:57,986 --> 00:12:59,029
(PLAYS A CHORD)

296
00:12:59,112 --> 00:13:00,822
'KAY, BUT FASTER.
FASTER.

297
00:13:00,906 --> 00:13:01,823
(MIMICS GUITAR CHORD)

298
00:13:01,907 --> 00:13:02,991
(STRUMS CHORD REPEATEDLY)

299
00:13:03,075 --> 00:13:04,076
YEAH! NICE!

300
00:13:06,537 --> 00:13:07,371
COME ON,
I NEED THIS TO WORK.

301
00:13:07,454 --> 00:13:08,664
MY DAD DOESN'T
PICK ME UP 'TIL 5:00.

302
00:13:08,747 --> 00:13:10,249
WE HAVE NOWHERE ELSE
TO GO.

303
00:13:10,332 --> 00:13:11,917
(PLAYS CHORDS FASTER)

304
00:13:13,001 --> 00:13:14,753
DANNY, FOLLOW SAV.

305
00:13:14,837 --> 00:13:15,838
DO IT!

306
00:13:16,547 --> 00:13:18,257
(DANNY PLAYS ALONG
WITH SAV'S RHYTHM)

307
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:19,758
(TURNS UP VOLUME)

308
00:13:24,096 --> 00:13:26,473
♪ I'M NOT A PRETTY BOY! ♪

309
00:13:26,557 --> 00:13:28,392
♪ I'M NOT A PRETTY BOY! ♪

310
00:13:28,475 --> 00:13:31,395
♪ I'M NOT A PRETTY BOY! ♪
AAAAAGH!

311
00:13:31,478 --> 00:13:33,856
(MICROPHONE FEEDBACK SQUEALS)

312
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:36,817
SAV:
DUDE!

313
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:38,485
THAT WAS AWESOME!

314
00:13:38,569 --> 00:13:40,070
WHO KNEW YOU WERE
SO PISSED OFF?

315
00:13:40,153 --> 00:13:41,864
THAT FELT GOOD.

316
00:13:41,947 --> 00:13:43,657
WE NEED A NAME.

317
00:13:46,827 --> 00:13:49,413
YOUR DAD HAVING AN AFFAIR?
WOW.

318
00:13:50,455 --> 00:13:52,040
THAT IS SUCH A SHOCK.

319
00:13:52,124 --> 00:13:53,041
ALL THIS TIME

320
00:13:53,125 --> 00:13:55,210
I HAVE TRIED TO LIVE UP
TO THE STANDARDS

321
00:13:55,294 --> 00:13:58,046
OF A MAN
WHO DOESN'T HAVE ANY.

322
00:13:58,130 --> 00:14:00,132
I AM SO SORRY, JIMMY.

323
00:14:01,216 --> 00:14:03,135
I TRIED TO DO EVERYTHING
TO MAKE HIM HAPPY.

324
00:14:03,218 --> 00:14:04,219
I...

325
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,390
LISTEN.

326
00:14:08,473 --> 00:14:11,435
MAYBE IT'S TIME TO DO
WHAT MAKES YOU HAPPY.

327
00:14:11,518 --> 00:14:13,854
GO AFTER WHAT'S YOURS.

328
00:14:15,689 --> 00:14:19,067
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW RIGHT YOU ARE.

329
00:14:20,903 --> 00:14:22,654
(HEAVY EXHALE)

330
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:25,407
(PUNK ROCK PLAYS)

331
00:14:25,490 --> 00:14:27,534
PETER:
♪ ALL WE EVER HAVE TO LOVE ♪

332
00:14:27,618 --> 00:14:29,870
♪ SHARED CUSTODY!
SHARED CUSTODY! ♪

333
00:14:29,953 --> 00:14:32,748
♪ ALTERNATE WEEKENDS
AND HOLIDAYS ♪

334
00:14:32,831 --> 00:14:34,833
♪ TWICE THE GIFTS
TWICE THE GIFTS ♪

335
00:14:34,917 --> 00:14:36,543
♪ BUT ALL WE EVER
HAVE TO LOVE ♪

336
00:14:39,213 --> 00:14:40,923
(MUSIC ENDS ABRUPTLY)

337
00:14:43,008 --> 00:14:45,511
DUDES?
THAT IS HARDCORE.

338
00:14:46,470 --> 00:14:47,387
AWES!

339
00:14:47,471 --> 00:14:48,889
YOU GET ON THE SKINS,
I'LL SET UP THE CAMERA!

340
00:14:48,972 --> 00:14:51,141
WHOA, WHOA!

341
00:14:51,225 --> 00:14:52,142
CAMERA?

342
00:14:52,226 --> 00:14:54,061
TO MAKE A VIDEO.
POST IT ON THE INTERNET.

343
00:14:54,144 --> 00:14:56,772
SHOW EVERYONE
HOW MUCH ASS WE KICK.

344
00:14:56,855 --> 00:14:58,357
PETER, LOOK,

345
00:14:58,440 --> 00:15:00,108
MAYBE YOU AND I CAN
BE SEEN TOGETHER...

346
00:15:00,192 --> 00:15:01,818
LIKE AS FRIENDS?

347
00:15:01,902 --> 00:15:03,529
SURE, FINE.

348
00:15:03,612 --> 00:15:05,948
BUT THOSE GUYS,
THEY'RE LIKE, THEY'RE NINERS.

349
00:15:06,031 --> 00:15:07,950
I'M IN ELEVEN.
SAV'S IN TEN.

350
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:08,951
YEAH.

351
00:15:09,034 --> 00:15:11,578
WHATEVER.
GUYS, YOU'RE GOOD,

352
00:15:11,662 --> 00:15:13,622
BUT YOUR BAND STILL NEEDS
TO LOOK FOR A DRUMMER, OKAY?

353
00:15:13,705 --> 00:15:15,040
NO! THERE HAS TO BE
ANOTHER WAY.

354
00:15:15,123 --> 00:15:17,417
'KAY?
I HAVE AN IDEA.

355
00:15:18,418 --> 00:15:19,837
(OBJECTS CLATTER)

356
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:24,424
OKAY.

357
00:15:24,508 --> 00:15:26,426
THINK UH...
THINK KISS,

358
00:15:26,510 --> 00:15:29,513
INSANE CLOWN POSSE,
SLIP KNOT.

359
00:15:30,264 --> 00:15:32,683
AN INCOGNITO BAND?

360
00:15:32,766 --> 00:15:36,186
THAT'S ACTUALLY
A PRETTY WICKED IDEA.

361
00:15:36,270 --> 00:15:37,604
(PUNK MUSIC PLAYS)

362
00:15:37,688 --> 00:15:40,023
PETER:
♪ SHARED CUSTODY!
SHARED CUSTODY! ♪

363
00:15:40,107 --> 00:15:42,693
♪ ALTERNATE WEEKENDS
AND HOLIDAYS ♪

364
00:15:42,776 --> 00:15:45,070
♪ TWICE THE GIFTS!
TWICE THE GIFTS! ♪

365
00:15:45,153 --> 00:15:46,446
♪ ALL WE EVER HAVE TO LOVE ♪

366
00:15:54,788 --> 00:15:55,831
(LOCK CLICKS)

367
00:16:00,711 --> 00:16:01,879
WAIT!

368
00:16:01,962 --> 00:16:03,547
ARE YOU CRAZY?

369
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:05,674
BREAKING IN?
THIS IS YOUR PLAN?

370
00:16:05,757 --> 00:16:09,011
JUST HURRY UP,
WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME.

371
00:16:14,725 --> 00:16:17,561
THIS ISN'T STEALING
BECAUSE...?

372
00:16:17,644 --> 00:16:20,230
IT'S MY MONEY
FOR MY FUTURE,

373
00:16:20,314 --> 00:16:22,065
AND I'M LOOKING INTO IT
RIGHT NOW.

374
00:16:22,149 --> 00:16:23,817
MMMM.
WHAT CAN I SAY?

375
00:16:23,901 --> 00:16:25,110
YOUR FUTURE
LOOKS VERY BRIGHT.

376
00:16:25,194 --> 00:16:26,195
MM-MM.

377
00:16:29,615 --> 00:16:31,325
PASS ME THE FORM.

378
00:16:32,743 --> 00:16:34,494
OKAY.

379
00:16:34,578 --> 00:16:37,915
AUTHORIZED BY...
JEMAINE BROOKS.

380
00:16:37,998 --> 00:16:38,999
(STAMP CLICKS)

381
00:16:41,001 --> 00:16:42,211
TRINA:
SO YOU TAKE THIS
TO THE BANK?

382
00:16:42,294 --> 00:16:43,170
THEY GIVE US THE CASH

383
00:16:43,253 --> 00:16:45,422
AND WE ARE ON OUR WAY
TO AMSTERDAM.

384
00:16:47,174 --> 00:16:48,175
MMM.

385
00:16:49,134 --> 00:16:51,178
(WHISPERS)
COME ON.

386
00:16:54,348 --> 00:16:55,933
DARCY:
SO, ARE WE STILL ON
FOR TONIGHT?

387
00:16:56,016 --> 00:16:56,850
PETER:
OH, TONIGHT?
I CAN'T.

388
00:16:56,934 --> 00:16:59,228
I'M UH, HANGING OUT
WITH THE GUYS.

389
00:16:59,311 --> 00:17:01,355
GUYS? WHO ARE THEY?

390
00:17:05,484 --> 00:17:07,152
CAN WE HELP YOU?

391
00:17:07,236 --> 00:17:08,946
WE DOIN' OUR SECRET THING
LATER, PETE?

392
00:17:09,029 --> 00:17:10,948
OH, SECRETS.
HOW CUTE!

393
00:17:11,031 --> 00:17:12,282
WHAT'RE YOU GUYS
GONNA DO EXACTLY?

394
00:17:12,366 --> 00:17:14,993
YOU KNOW, GUY STUFF:
EATING AND BELCHING.

395
00:17:15,077 --> 00:17:16,787
MAKING FUN OF SAV'S
STICKER BOOK.

396
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:18,121
VERY FUNNY.

397
00:17:18,205 --> 00:17:19,873
DARCY:
OKAY, WELL...

398
00:17:19,957 --> 00:17:21,083
HAVE FUN.

399
00:17:21,166 --> 00:17:22,876
PETER:
WE WILL!

400
00:17:28,382 --> 00:17:29,508
UH, HEY!

401
00:17:29,591 --> 00:17:31,260
NO SKETCHY BUSINESS,
OKAY?

402
00:17:31,343 --> 00:17:33,178
DARCY, TRUST ME.

403
00:17:37,391 --> 00:17:38,600
JIMMY:
(TIRED SIGH)

404
00:17:38,684 --> 00:17:40,310
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
AFTER SCHOOL?

405
00:17:40,394 --> 00:17:42,104
SPINNER:
UM...

406
00:17:42,187 --> 00:17:43,188
NOTHING.

407
00:17:44,231 --> 00:17:45,482
REALLY. NOTHING.

408
00:17:47,150 --> 00:17:49,152
MR. BROOKS:
JIMMY?

409
00:17:49,736 --> 00:17:51,655
SEE YOU LATER.

410
00:17:53,907 --> 00:17:55,450
MR. BROOKS:
MY BANK MANAGER
CALLED ME THIS MORNING.

411
00:17:55,534 --> 00:17:58,161
SOMEONE ACCESSED
THE TRUST FUND MONEY.

412
00:17:58,245 --> 00:17:59,496
ANY EXPLANATION?

413
00:17:59,580 --> 00:18:01,665
WELL, LIKE YOU SAY, SIR.

414
00:18:01,748 --> 00:18:03,876
"YOU MISS 100% OF THE SHOTS
YOU DON'T TAKE."

415
00:18:03,959 --> 00:18:05,127
AH.

416
00:18:05,210 --> 00:18:08,172
SO WE HAVE THEFT,
FORGERY...

417
00:18:08,255 --> 00:18:11,258
AND LET'S NOT FORGET
ADULTERY.

418
00:18:15,262 --> 00:18:17,890
I SAW YOU LAST NIGHT
WITH MELANIE.

419
00:18:17,973 --> 00:18:19,808
MELANIE AT WORK?

420
00:18:19,892 --> 00:18:21,351
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

421
00:18:21,435 --> 00:18:22,603
I WENT TO YOUR OFFICE

422
00:18:22,686 --> 00:18:25,564
TO TELL YOU THAT I WANTED
THE INTERNSHIP.

423
00:18:25,647 --> 00:18:29,318
I SAW YOU TWO
AND THEN LEFT.

424
00:18:29,401 --> 00:18:30,986
WE WERE WORKING LATE.
THAT'S ALL.

425
00:18:31,069 --> 00:18:32,988
LOOK,
I'M NOT AN IDIOT.

426
00:18:33,780 --> 00:18:38,076
SHE WAS ALL OVER YOU
AND YOU DIDN'T SEEM TO MIND.

427
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:40,204
LOOK, JIMMY,
SOMETIMES MELANIE...

428
00:18:40,287 --> 00:18:41,705
LET ME GUESS,

429
00:18:41,788 --> 00:18:44,958
SHE MANIPULATES POOR,
INNOCENT YOU?

430
00:18:45,959 --> 00:18:47,377
LOOK,
JUST RETURN THE MONEY

431
00:18:47,461 --> 00:18:51,006
AND THIS DOESN'T
HAVE TO GO ANY FURTHER.

432
00:18:51,089 --> 00:18:54,092
THEN HOW DO I GET
TO AMSTERDAM?

433
00:18:57,971 --> 00:18:59,973
SEE YOU AT DINNER.

434
00:19:05,062 --> 00:19:08,398
(STUDZ SONG PLAYS
THROUGH HEADPHONES)

435
00:19:10,567 --> 00:19:12,277
WHAT IS THAT NOISE?

436
00:19:12,361 --> 00:19:14,279
IT'S NOT NOISE.
IT'S AWESOMENESS.

437
00:19:14,363 --> 00:19:16,865
IS THAT STUDZ?
THEY'RE SO RAD!

438
00:19:16,949 --> 00:19:18,242
WAIT, WHY AM I
SO OUT OF THE LOOP?

439
00:19:18,325 --> 00:19:20,786
THEY'RE THIS DEGRASSI BAND.
NOBODY KNOWS WHO THEY ARE.

440
00:19:20,869 --> 00:19:22,663
SPIN IS GONNA LOVE THEM.

441
00:19:22,746 --> 00:19:24,081
PETER:
ONE-TWO-THREE-FOUR!

442
00:19:24,164 --> 00:19:26,542
♪ SHARED CUSTODY!
SHARED CUSTODY! ♪

443
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:29,920
♪ ALTERNATE WEEKENDS
AND HOLIDAYS ♪

444
00:19:30,003 --> 00:19:31,922
IS THAT BLOOD?

445
00:19:32,005 --> 00:19:33,590
OR RED PAINT?

446
00:19:33,674 --> 00:19:34,633
OH MY GOSH.

447
00:19:35,551 --> 00:19:37,427
IS THAT...?
ARE YOU...?

448
00:19:37,511 --> 00:19:39,513
SHHH. IT'S A SECRET.

449
00:19:39,596 --> 00:19:42,432
IT'S A SIDE PROJECT
FOR ME AND MY FRIENDS.

450
00:19:42,516 --> 00:19:43,684
(CHUCKLES)

451
00:19:47,020 --> 00:19:48,689
(LOW HUM OF CHATTER)

452
00:19:49,857 --> 00:19:52,025
SORRY I'M LATE.
MMM.

453
00:19:53,235 --> 00:19:54,361
HAVE YOU ORDERED?

454
00:19:54,444 --> 00:19:55,362
NO.

455
00:19:55,445 --> 00:19:56,780
THE MUSSELS LOOK GOOD.

456
00:19:56,864 --> 00:19:59,199
MRS. BROOKS:
WAIT A MINUTE.
SINCE WHEN DO YOU LIKE MUSSELS?

457
00:19:59,283 --> 00:20:01,535
OH, THE THINGS
YOU DON'T KNOW.

458
00:20:01,618 --> 00:20:04,955
MRS. BROOKS:
WHAT'S THAT, SWEETIE?

459
00:20:05,497 --> 00:20:08,417
MOM, DAD AND I HAD
A TALK TODAY.

460
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,294
WE MADE A BREAKTHROUGH.

461
00:20:10,377 --> 00:20:12,421
YOU DID?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

462
00:20:13,547 --> 00:20:17,634
WOULD YOU LIKE TO TELL HER,
OR SHOULD I?

463
00:20:17,718 --> 00:20:20,971
JIMMY AND I HAD ANOTHER TALK
ABOUT THE STEM-CELL TREATMENT

464
00:20:21,054 --> 00:20:22,139
AND UH, HE MADE A CASE

465
00:20:22,222 --> 00:20:24,349
THAT WOULD STAND UP
IN ANY COURT OF LAW.

466
00:20:24,433 --> 00:20:26,268
I WAS IMPRESSED.

467
00:20:27,895 --> 00:20:29,354
I'D LIKE TO USE
MY TRUST FUND MONEY

468
00:20:29,438 --> 00:20:32,191
AND GET IT DONE
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

469
00:20:32,274 --> 00:20:34,318
I'M SURPRISED, JEMAINE,
YOU KNOW THE RISKS.

470
00:20:34,401 --> 00:20:36,028
AND WE TALKED ABOUT
GETTING HIS HOPES UP.

471
00:20:36,111 --> 00:20:37,029
JIMMY:
MOM...

472
00:20:37,112 --> 00:20:39,156
TALK TO ME.

473
00:20:39,239 --> 00:20:41,909
'KAY, MAYBE IT WON'T WORK;
I CAN LIVE WITH THAT.

474
00:20:41,992 --> 00:20:45,662
BUT I CAN'T LIVE WITHOUT
NOT EVEN TRYING.

475
00:20:48,290 --> 00:20:49,541
I THINK HE DESERVES
A CHANCE.

476
00:20:51,251 --> 00:20:53,003
YOU'RE SURE ABOUT THIS,
JIMMY?

477
00:20:54,004 --> 00:20:55,005
YEAH.

478
00:21:01,929 --> 00:21:02,930
OKAY.

479
00:21:03,931 --> 00:21:05,682
(ELATED BREATH)

480
00:21:08,602 --> 00:21:09,603
THANK YOU.

481
00:21:13,106 --> 00:21:14,107
OKAY.

482
